    • getBestMove

      public String getBestMove(String fen, int waitTime)
      Gets a move from Stockfish and parses it into coordinates if found
      Parameters:
      fen - A FEN string that represents the board
      waitTime - The amount of time that Stockfish should wait before responding
      Returns:
      The coordinates from and two to move ex. a2a4 is move white pawn up two squares. or null if the move in not received

    • getOutput

      public String getOutput(int waitTime)
      This is generally called right after 'sendCommand' for getting the raw output from Stockfish
      Parameters:
      waitTime - Time in milliseconds for which the function waits before reading the output. Useful when a long running command is executed
      Returns:
      Raw output from Stockfish
